});
```

The key change is replacing:
```javascript
assert.approximately(result5.re, 1.5, 0.0001);
assert.approximately(result5.im, 2.7, 0.0001);
```

with:
```javascript
assert.ok(Math.abs(result5.re - 1.5) < 0.0001);
assert.ok(Math.abs(result5.im - 2.7) < 0.0001);
```

This uses `assert.ok()` with `Math.abs()` to check that the difference between the actual and expected values is within the specified tolerance.

